text: Francisco Guadarrama López (born 10 October 1947) is a Mexican politician from the National Action Party. From 2000 to 2003 he served as Deputy of the LVIII Legislature of the Mexican Congress representing the State of Mexico. ==References== Category:1947 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from the State of Mexico Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Mexico) Category:National Action Party (Mexico) politicians Category:21st-century Mexican politicians
